From Gordon Banks Subject Re Name of MD's eyepiece In article C IHM G Ed Clarke writes It's not an eyepiece It is called a head mirror All doctors never A speculum The speculum is the little cone that fits on the end of the otoscope There are also vaginal specula that females and gynecologists are all too familiar with Gordon Banks N JXP Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect, and it is shameful to surrender it too soon